RELEASE INFORMATION

Project:           Distro Changes Analyzer (distdiff)
Version:           1.0
Date:              2013-04-10


This file explains how to install and setup environment
for the tool in your computer.


Content:

   1. Requirements for Linux and FreeBSD
   2. Requirements for Mac OS X
   3. Configuring and Installing
   4. Running the Tool


1. REQUIREMENTS FOR LINUX AND FREEBSD
=====================================

   1. Perl 5 (5.8 or newer)
   2. PkgDiff (1.5 or newer)
   3. GNU Diff
   4. GNU Wdiff
   5. GNU Awk
   6. GNU Binutils (readelf)

1.1 Analysis of RPM packages

   RPM (rpm, rpm2cpio)

1.2 Analysis of DEB packages

   DPKG (dpkg, dpkg-deb)



2. REQUIREMENTS FOR MAC OS X
============================

   1. Perl 5 (5.8 or newer)
   2. PkgDiff (1.5 or newer)
   3. GNU Diff
   4. GNU Wdiff
   5. GNU Awk
   6. Xcode (otool)



3. CONFIGURING AND INSTALLING
=============================

   This command will install an distdiff program in the
   PREFIX/bin system directory and private modules into the PREFIX/share:

     sudo perl Makefile.pl -install --prefix=PREFIX [/usr, /usr/local, ...]

2.1 Update

     sudo perl Makefile.pl -update --prefix=PREFIX

2.2 Remove

     sudo perl Makefile.pl -remove --prefix=PREFIX



4. RUNNING THE TOOL
===================

   1. distdiff DIR1 DIR2
   
   DIR1 and DIR2 - directories with old and new packages of the Linux distribution (RPM, DEB, TAR.GZ, etc)
   
   2. For advanced usage, see output of --help option



Enjoy!
